## IAM — consumer permissions

Consumers (Lambdas, ECS tasks) receive **only** the actions they need. Never grant `dynamodb:*`.

| Consumer | Actions | Scope |
|----------|---------|-------|
| *(service name)* | `GetItem, PutItem, UpdateItem, Query` | table ARN + GSI ARNs |
| *(read-only service)* | `GetItem, Query` | table ARN + GSI ARNs |

{{#if enableResourcePolicy}}
## Cross-account resource policy (PCI)

PCI account `{{pciAccountId}}` granted via `aws_dynamodb_resource_policy`:
- `dynamodb:GetItem`
- `dynamodb:PutItem`
- `dynamodb:Query`

Scope: table ARN only. **No** GSI access, no `UpdateItem`, no `DeleteItem` (requires explicit justification + security approval).
{{/if}}

## Observability

- CloudWatch alarms: `UserErrors >= 1`, `SystemErrors >= 1`, `ThrottledRequests >= 1` on table + each GSI. Forward to SNS `alerts-{env}`.
{{#eq billingMode "PROVISIONED"}}
- Additional alarms: `ConsumedReadCapacityUnits > 80%` of provisioned, `ConsumedWriteCapacityUnits > 80%` of provisioned.
{{/eq}}
- Dashboard widgets: item count, table size, consumed read/write capacity, throttled requests.

## Variables needed in platform repo

Add to `terraform/variables.auto.tfvars` (or already inherited from `common.tf`):
- `business_domain`, `service_domain`, `project_name`, `version_project`, `owner` — global vars.
- `deletion_protection_enabled` — per-environment override (false in dev/qa, true in prod).
- `ttl_attribute_name` — `"{{#if ttlEnabled}}{{ttlAttributeName}}{{else}}null{{/if}}"`.
{{#if enableResourcePolicy}}
- `pci_account` — injected from Terraform Cloud workspace variables (secret).
{{/if}}
